        <title>Sheet Metal Workers International Assn. v. Lynn</title>
        <section startTime="0.000" stopTime="7.639">
          <heading>Announcement of Chief Justice Rehnquist</heading>
          <turn speaker="william_h_rehnquist" startTime="0.000" stopTime="7.639">
            <label>Chief Justice Rehnquist</label>
            <text syncTime="0.000" offset="86552">The opinion of the Court in number 86-1940, Sheet Metal Workers versus Lynn will be announced by Justice Marshall.</text>
          </turn>
        </section>
        <section startTime="7.639" stopTime="57.730">
          <heading>Announcement of Justice Marshall</heading>
          <turn speaker="thurgood_marshall" startTime="7.639" stopTime="57.730">
            <label>Justice Thurgood Marshall</label>
            <text syncTime="7.639" offset="117063">This case is here on writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit.</text>
            <text syncTime="13.995" offset="142454">In an Opinion filed with the clerk today, we hold that the removal of an elected Union official in retaliation for statements he made at a Union meeting in opposition to a deuced increase sought by a Union trustee violated the Labor Management Reporting and Disclosed Act 1959.</text>
            <text syncTime="44.034" offset="262617">The Court of Appeals? judgment is, thereby, affirmed.</text>
            <text syncTime="47.591" offset="276828">Justice White has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment.</text>
            <text syncTime="51.981" offset="294382">Justice Kennedy took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.</text>
          </turn>
        </section>
